      { time: '3:30 PM', name: 'Ortaköy — mosque & kumpir', note: 'Take a taxi or bus west along the Bosphorus to Ortaköy, a charming waterfront neighbourhood beneath the Bosphorus Bridge. The ornate Baroque Ortaköy Mosque sits directly on the water with the suspension bridge towering above. The neighbourhood is famous for kumpir — a giant baked potato loaded with toppings, sold from street carts right by the mosque.', food: 'Kumpir from a street cart in Ortaköy — with cheese, corn, olives, sautéed mushrooms' },
      { time: '6:30 PM', name: 'Final evening in Istanbul', note: 'Return along the Bosphorus to the old city. Take a last walk around Sultanahmet at dusk — when the Blue Mosque and Hagia Sophia are illuminated and the muezzin call echoes across the city, it is genuinely one of the great sounds in the world.' },
      { time: '8:30 PM', name: 'Last dinner — Sultanahmet or Beyoğlu', note: 'Final Istanbul dinner. Go somewhere you haven\'t been yet — explore a meyhane in the Pera neighbourhood or a fish restaurant on the Bosphorus shore.', food: 'Balıkçı Sabahattin (Sultanahmet) — one of Istanbul\'s most celebrated fish restaurants, been open since 1927' },
