      { time: 'Morning', name: 'Final simit & çay', note: 'One last simit from a street cart, one last glass of çay watching the Bosphorus. The morning call to prayer, the ferries crossing the water, the seagulls. This is how you remember Istanbul.', food: 'Simit from any street cart — the essential Istanbul street food' },
      { time: 'Afternoon', name: 'Last wander & gifts', note: 'Pick up any remaining souvenirs: Turkish delight, pistachio cream, saffron, ceramics, good tea. The Grand Bazaar opens at 8:30 AM on weekdays. Check out of the hotel and store bags at the front desk while you wander.' },
